title: Install OS X El Capitan.app
description:
Fresh copy of OS X El Capitan downloaded directly from the Mac App Store, no alterations whatsoever.

I compressed it into a .zip file merely by going to File > Compress

This did not modify the original install file, it merely "copied" it to a .zip folder.

This will work with Unibeast, but to use Unibeast you need an existing Mac! If you don't have an existing Mac, please don't ask Hackintosh related questions!

I will try to seed this 24/7, if it's not downloading, it's probably because my computer is off! Just keep the file active in your client and wait until the download picks up again!

Enjoy!

************

Instructions:

************

For Mac users:

1. Insert USB drive 16 GB or larger

2. Open Finder > Applications > Utilities > Disk Utility

3. Highlight your USB in Disk Utility and hit the erase tab. 

4. Name the USB "Untitled" (without quotations) and make sure it's set to Mac OS X Extended Journaled and hit erase

5. Extract the .zip file downloaded, and copy the Install OS X El Capitan.app to > Finder > Applications

6. Copy & Paste this command into terminal:

sudo /Applications/Install OS X El Capitan.app/Contents/Resources/createinstallmedia --volume /Volumes/Untitled --applicationpath /Applications/Install OS X El Capitan.app --nointeraction

7. Safely eject the USB in finder.

8. Enjoy!
